title: The Adventures of Sinbad the sailor
creator_contributor_role: Victorian Council for Children's Films and Television, distributor
subject_group: Advertising, Film, Journalism, Mass Media & TV/Sea in motion pictures
description: Episode of Series "Storytime Collection". Young Sinbad receives a map from "The Old Man of the Sea" to an island where jewels and treasures are hidden within a cave. Whilst searching for the treasure he falls in love with a Princess; is thrown into jail and manages to escape with her help. The Princess is already engaged to the Evil Prime Minister who follows Sinbad to the treasure island. A fierce battle ensues and the island along with the treasure disappears into the sea. Sinbad and the Princess realise that the love they have for each other is worth more than any treasure. No other production details available.
